# Weather Microservice

This project is a microservice for fetching weather information from various cities around the world. It is built using Node.js, Express, and integrates Swagger for API documentation.

weather-microservice/
│
├── api/
│   ├── weather.js          # Controllers for handling API routes
│   └── swagger.yaml        # Swagger specification
│
├── node_modules/           # Installed npm dependencies
│
├── app.js                  # Main entry point of the application
├── package.json            # npm configuration file
└── README.md               # Project documentation


## Features

- Fetch current weather information by city name.
- API documentation using Swagger UI.
- Containerized using Docker for easy deployment.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js (v14 or higher)
- npm (v6 or higher)
- Docker (for containerization)

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone <repository-url>
   cd weather-microservice

2. Build Project
    
  Set your OpenWeatherMap API key in api/weather.js:
  const apiKey = '36186da6-3a54-11ef-899d-0242ac130004-36186e1e-3a54-11ef-899d-0242ac130004';

3. Build the Docker Image
   To build the Docker image
   docker build -t clima-microservicio .
   docker run -p 3000:3000 --name clima-container clima-microservicio

### The server will start on http://localhost:3000/api/weather/Quito

### API Documentation
    Swagger UI is available at http://localhost:3000/api-docs.

